# Reference copy — committed defaults live in `.env` (tracked for self-hosted / non-Vercel deploys).
# Override locally with `.env.local` (gitignored) for secrets or machine-specific values.
#
# ============ API CONFIG (src/lib/api.ts) ============

# Listings — browser hits this path. Your host must proxy /api/listings like api/listings.ts, or set a full URL.
# Omit to default to /api/listings (see src/lib/api.ts).
VITE_LISTINGS_URL=/api/listings
# Optional: extra query for local /api/listings (parameter names depend on Ruuster—ask them for sort/limit keys).
# VITE_LISTINGS_QUERY=limit=200
# How often to refetch listings when tab is visible (ms). Min 10000 in code; default 45000 if unset.
VITE_LISTINGS_POLL_MS=10000
# Or base URL: VITE_API_BASE=https://yoursite.com

# Leads - Formspree or custom
VITE_FORMSPREE_ID=
VITE_LEADS_ENDPOINT=

# ============ LISTINGS PROXY (api/listings.ts or your host’s equivalent) ============
# Values are in `.env` for git. On any host, the proxy must forward to Ruuster with status=Active + these params.
# Local: `npm run dev` uses vite.config.ts to proxy /api/listings (reads RUUSTER_LISTINGS_EXTRA_PARAMS from .env).
#
# Base URL (default already points to Red Post's Ruuster tenant):
# RUUSTER_API_URL=https://redpostrealty.ruuster.com/api
#
# REQUIRED: agent slug scopes the public endpoint — no API key needed.
# Confirmed via GET /api/listings?slug=sarah-hudson&status=Active&limit=500 → 200 OK (66 records).
# Adjust `limit` to taste; `status=Active` is forced by the proxy. Other valid keys from
# Ruuster's basedFilterOptions: sortBy (newest|priceHL|priceLH|bedsHL|sqftHL|lotSizeHL|bathHL|priceReduced|oldest).
RUUSTER_LISTINGS_EXTRA_PARAMS=slug=sarah-hudson&limit=500&sortBy=newest
#
# After changing these, restart your host / rebuild so the listings proxy picks them up.
#
# Optional: only set if Ruuster ever adds an authenticated endpoint for this tenant.
# RUUSTER_API_KEY=
